article.headline: Coastal Carolina 79, Radford 61
article.story: CONWAY, S.C. (AP) -- Freshman Jack Leasure scored 22 points to lead Coastal Carolina to a 79-61 victory over Radford on Monday night. The Chanticleers (9-14, 6-5 Big South Conference) won their second straight game as four players scored in double figures. Coastal took the lead for good on Pele Paelay's basket that made it 42-41 with 16:44 remaining and began a 7-0 run. The Highlanders (10-12, 5-6) got within four points, but couldn't make it any closer. Coastal Carolina took control of the game after that with a 12-1 over a five minute stretch of the second half. Alvin Green scored 14 points, Paelay 12 and Noah Nichols 10 for the Chants. Brandon Jeffers and Chris Oliver had 17 points each to lead Radford.
